# Machine Learning Portfolio Rules

## Brand palette

Use `common/portfolio_style.py` for all plots. Do not invent new brand colors.

| Name | Hex |
|------|-----|
| Light Blue | `#8fd7d7` |
| Med Blue | `#00b0be` |
| Light Pink | `#ff8ca1` |
| Med Pink | `#f45f74` |
| Light Green | `#bdd373` |
| Med Green | `#98c127` |
| Light Orange | `#ffcd8e` |
| Med Orange | `#ffb255` |

Chart defaults: class 0 / primary → Med Blue; class 1 / secondary → Med Pink; best-model highlight → Med Blue; fills/heatmaps → light variants; extra series → Med Green / Med Orange. Neutrals for text/axes only.

## Public presentation (recruiter-facing)

- Public READMEs and notebook narrative must read as professional portfolio work.
- Never mention courses, homework, assignments, school deadlines, or converting school projects in committed docs or notebooks.
- Prefer clear problem → method → results framing.

## Private project hygiene (do not put in public READMEs)

- Use descriptive kebab-case folder names (e.g. `fashion-coat-dress-classification`).
- Avoid course codes or assignment numbers in public folder names and titles.
- Keep large raw datasets out of git unless they are small enough to ship with the project.

